@startuml
title WOF Portal — IHE ITI Scheduling Flow

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderThickness 1
skinparam noteBorderColor #888888
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFEE

actor Patient
boundary "Portal\n(Scheduling Client)" as Client
control "WOF Portal Server\n(Scheduling Server)" as Server

== 1. Pre-booking Context (WOF Portal custom) ==

note over Client,Server
  Operation loads booking content quickly so the patient can choose
  what to book, with whom, and where, avoiding multiple round trips
end note

Client -> Server : POST [base]/ActivityDefinition/{id}/$getOffersContext\n(includeActivityDefinitionPortal, includeHealthcareServicePortal, includePractitionerRolePortal)
Server --> Client : 200 OK — **BundleOffersContextPortal** (searchset)\n ├─ ActivityDefinitionPortal  (what is being booked)\n ├─ HealthcareServicePortal    (where)\n ├─ PractitionerRolePortal     (who)\n └─ OfferPortal                (combination + booking rules)

Patient <-- Client : Displays treatments, clinics, practitioners
Patient -> Client : Selects ActivityDefinition + HealthcareService\n + PractitionerRole (via OfferPortal)

== 2. Find Available Times — $find ==

note over Client,Server
  Find Potential Appointments
  Returns **proposed** Appointments (status = proposed).
end note

Client -> Server : POST [base]/Appointment/$find\n(start, end, healthcareService, practitionerRole, visit-type, ...)
Server --> Client : 200 OK — **WofConnectFindAppointment Bundle** (searchset)\n └─ AppointmentPortal[*]  status = **proposed**

Patient <-- Client : Displays available times

opt Patient selects a time
  Patient -> Client : Selects time (AppointmentPortal.id)
end

== 3a. Book Appointment — $book CREATE ==

note over Client,Server
  Book selected Appointment
  appointment.id = absent/new, then status = pending → CREATE
end note

Client -> Server : POST [base]/Appointment/$book\n(appointment: AppointmentPortal {status=pending}, patient-resource, comment?)
Server --> Client : 200 OK — **ihe-sched-avail-bundle**\n └─ AppointmentPortal  status = **booked**

Patient <-- Client : Booking confirmed

== 3b. Modify Appointment — $book MODIFY ==

note over Client,Server
  appointment.id = existing, status = booked → MODIFY
end note

Client -> Server : POST [base]/Appointment/$book\n(appointment: AppointmentPortal {id=existing, status=booked, updated details})
Server --> Client : 200 OK — **ihe-sched-avail-bundle**\n └─ AppointmentPortal  status = **booked** (updated)

Patient <-- Client : Modification confirmed

== 3c. Cancel Appointment — $book CANCEL ==

note over Client,Server
  appointment.id = existing, status = cancelled → CANCEL
end note

Client -> Server : POST [base]/Appointment/$book\n(appointment: AppointmentPortal {id=existing, status=cancelled})
Server --> Client : 200 OK — **ihe-sched-avail-bundle**\n └─ AppointmentPortal  status = **cancelled**

Patient <-- Client : Cancellation confirmed

== Error Handling (all operations) ==

Client -> Server : POST [base]/Appointment/$book or $find
Server --> Client : 4xx/5xx — **OperationOutcome**

@enduml
